modules.description: Provides functions for scheduling and managing timeouts in a way that integrates with event loops. Operates on integers representing time intervals and callbacks with unit return types. Used to implement asynchronous operations that must yield control to the scheduler after a specified duration.

Provides functions to manage file descriptors, including closing, reading, writing, creating pipes, and performing selective I/O operations with timeouts. Operates on file descriptors and byte buffers for low-level communication. Used to implement timeout mechanisms for domain-local network or process communication.
